---
title: Chicken Chile Verde Instant Pot
---

Combine @chicken thighs and drumsticks{3%lbs} (bone-in, skin-on), @poblano peppers{1%lb}, roughly chopped with seeds and stems discarded (about 3 peppers), @tomatillos{12%oz}, husks discarded and quartered (about 4), @white onion{10%oz}, roughly chopped (about 1 medium), @Anaheim or Cubanelle peppers{6%oz}, roughly chopped with seeds and stems discarded (about 2 peppers), @Serrano or jalape√±o peppers{2}, roughly chopped with stems discarded, @garlic cloves{6%medium}, peeled, @whole cumin seeds{1%tbsp}, toasted and ground, and a big pinch of @kosher salt{} in a #pressure cooker{}. Heat over high heat until gently sizzling, then seal the pressure cooker, bring to high pressure, and cook for ~{15%minutes}. Release pressure.

Using tongs, transfer chicken pieces to a bowl and set aside. Add @fresh cilantro{1/2%cup}, loosely packed leaves and fine stems, and @Asian fish sauce{1%tbsp} to the remaining contents of the pressure cooker. Blend with an immersion blender or in a countertop blender and season to taste with salt. Return chicken to sauce, discarding skin and bones and shredding if desired.

Transfer to a serving platter, garnish with chopped cilantro, and serve immediately with @fresh corn tortillas{} and @lime wedges{}.
